Why this split?
---------------
AGPL-3.0 on the software ensures anyone who runs a modified copy
of UNHRD as a hosted service must release their modifications
under the same licence — closing the "SaaS loophole" that GPL-
only would leave open.

CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 on the curated dataset preserves academic re-use
(researchers, NGOs, treaty body members are free to use, share,
and build upon) while preventing third-party commercial
exploitation of the curation work.

